Station Update - Sydenham

Platforms 4, 5 & 6 upgrade works. A new Metro concourse is being constructed on the northern end of Sydenham Station. While the concourse is being installed, please board and alight from the first 5 carriages of the train on platforms 4 & 6 and the last 6 carriages of the train on platform 5. If you need help, please ask staff at the station. For more information on these upgrades, please see sydneymetro.info
https://transportnsw.info/alerts#/train
Station Update - Bexley North, Redfern
Due to station redevelopment work some platforms have reduced capacity. Please avoid standing in front of construction zones and remain behind the yellow line on the platform
https://transportnsw.info/alerts#/train
Station Update - Central

There are changes happening at Central Station due to Sydney Metro construction works. Access to certain areas of the station and platforms may mean using different stairs, escalators and lifts. Please follow the signs and staff directions. If you need assistance, see station staff. For detailed information please visit https://transportnsw.info/alerts/details#/6063489

Opal can be used between Bathurst and Lithgow Stations when booked

If travelling by Coach to or from Bathurst you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at Bathurst station and your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station. When using Opal you will need to reserve a seat, at no cost, through the Contact Centre by calling 13 22 32 (Between 07:00 to 22:00 each day).
